    The ppgg(1) command is a simple pager for reading files. If no file is
    specified, ppgg(1) reads the standard input. It accepts a very few commands,
    listed after the options.

    The ppgg(1) utility takes the following options:
    --nn lines
        Display lines number of lines at a time.

    This ppgg(1) implementation is very simple. It accepts the following
    commands while displaying a file; commands must be followed by ENTER:
    ??, hh,, HH
        Display help messages.

    qq
        Quit displaying current file and go on to the next file.

    QQ
        Quit entirely.

    EENNTTEERR
        Any other command (or simply ENTER) displays the next screen of text.

  DDIIAAGGNNOOSSTTIICCSS

